# =============================================================================
# NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Add project-specific patterns as needed
# 2. Never commit sensitive information (.env files, keys, passwords)
# 3. Use !pattern to force-include files that would otherwise be ignored
# 4. Test .gitignore changes with: git check-ignore -v <file>
# 5. Clean up already-tracked sensitive files with: git rm --cached <file>
# 6. Review this file periodically and update as the project grows
